Account-Level and Inter-Account Attack Path Analysis
============================================================

Simulate two accounts, both of which have been provisioned with all the aforementioned applications, and detect three attack paths.

Account 1:
  The account contains the following services:
    _FC_NAS_fc-llm, _FC_NAS_web-framework-1vwt, etu-ocr-20i3, fc-llm, fc-stable-diffusion-plus, serverless-devs-check, web-framework-1vwt
  Confirmed escalated permission: 
    ['fc:AddPermission', 'ram:AttachRolePolicy', 'ram:UpdateAssumeRolePolicy', 'sts:AssumeRole', 'ram:PassRole', 'ram:CreateRole', 'fc:CreateFunction', 'fc:UpdateFunctionConfiguration', 'ram:PutRolePolicy', 'fc:UpdateFunctionCode']

  The privilege escalation paths in Account 1:
    confirm: 'sts:AssumeRole' -> function_escalation_method1
    confirm: 'ram:CreateRole+ram:AttachRolePolicy' -> function_escalation_method1
    confirm: 'ram:PutRolePolicy' -> function_escalation_method1
    confirm: 'ram:UpdateAssumeRolePolicy' -> function_escalation_method1
    confirm: 'ram:PassRole+fc:CreateFunction' -> 'sts:AssumeRole' -> function_escalation_method2
    confirm: 'ram:PassRole+fc:CreateFunction' -> 'ram:CreateRole+ram:AttachRolePolicy' -> function_escalation_method2

    confirm: 'fc:UpdateFunctionCode' -> 'ram:CreateRole+ram:AttachRolePolicy' -> function_escalation_method2
    confirm: 'fc:UpdateFunctionCode' -> 'ram:PutRolePolicy' -> function_escalation_method2
    confirm: 'fc:UpdateFunctionCode' -> 'ram:UpdateAssumeRolePolicy' -> function_escalation_method2
